reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this Lamp!
reviews.reviewText: It works great and looks like the Pixar lamp. Now I wish I had bought the white one. It has a nice heave base and comes with clap attachment! Will look for a reason it get another.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works for my needs. However, the base needs to be heavier. It doesn't allow the lamp head to be position out farther. The screw down clamp is flimsy and needs to be wider to accommodate the longer extension of the lamp head.The lamp shade is a bit short, doesn't block the side light from small compact Fluorescent bulbs & LED bulbs. Works GREAT for incandescent bulbs!! But those are becoming (if not already) OBSOLETE!! Even most places in my area don't even sell appliance incandescent bulbs anymore.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value. A solid purchase
reviews.reviewText: Its' a little smaller than I had imagined. There are no adjustments for the tension of the sections of support though the stiffness makes it hold its position. I installed a "100 watt" equivalent LED bulb for task lighting and works well on the lamp. The switch is 1 foot down the cord which makes it inconvenient to turn off/on (in my opinion). Would be better on the light somewhere. As a base to place the lamp on a desk or similar and a clamp fixture for a bench or table. Neither is particularly robust but adequate. The clamp base aldo allows the lamp to be screwed permanent to a surface. Overall, I'm satisfied and the price is cheap.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great reading light
reviews.reviewText: We already have one of these lights clamped to the headboard of our bed. I have purchased this one for my side to read with. I drilled a couple holes through the clamping end and used screws to mount it to the wall that was convenient for me to see better. I highly recommend it. The company who sells them probably doesn’t want you to drill holes in the clamp to hang it but it doesn’t interfere with the wiring.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Lamp part works fine, arm part not so much
reviews.reviewText: It’s a decent enough lamp, especially for the price. But had I known about the base and clamp issues, I probably would have looked elsewhere. The base it too light; you can’t extend the arm too far out or the center of gravity shifts and it tips over. It will stay in the classic “lamp pose” just fine, but I bought this to put by my bed. I want it to be able to extend over/retract so that I can shine it down onto my bed as I do homework in my dormroom. And it can do that, but it has a far more limited range than it’s arm length would suggest due to it’s inability to not fall over when stretched that far. The clamp it comes with is also a bit of a joke. Can it work under ideal circumstances? Sure. But it’s fairly cheap feeling plastic (rest of the lamp body is metal), has a relatively tiny clamp diameter, doesn’t “lock” the lamp end into itself (it’s a friction fit for the clamp, the base has a thumbscrew you can tighten once you insert the lamp’s bottom so that it stays relatively secure), and does not have the strength/sturdiness to hold the lamp at anything but an upright configuration. You can’t clamp it sideways; it really can’t do anything that the base can’t do, except for save a tiny bit of space at the edge of your desk. I’m honestly not going to bother returning it, I will be using it for the foreseeable future because it does work fine. But if I happen to see a better one at a store or something, it’s probably going to get replaced. The build quality isn’t really there for how I wanted to use it, but it’s also not a knockoff or anything. It works, looks fine, and can get fairly bright depending on what bulb you put into it. I’m just disappointed by the balance issues, as well as the ineptitude of the clamp. Adding several ounces worth of weight to the base, and making the clamp strong enough to support the lamp sideways would easily make this product a 5/5, even if it meant increasing the price by 10 or 15 bucks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An Excellent artist's crane lamp!!
reviews.reviewText: I had another version of this type of a lamp for my art table, way back in the early 1990s and I had it for 6 years and somehow it started having electrical problems and then it blew out completely. After that, I've never bought another one. As for this one - this lamp is excellent and I like the round shaped base and the separate clamp part. This was a excellent purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this, not as a desk lamp but as alternative lighting for a 3 gallon jar with snails and live plants. I added a bulb intended for that purpose, but it was too bright and am using a simple 2500k led from the local chain store. (It works great for growing Salvinia, Java Moss and Java fern in that configuration fwiw.) Anyway, it is cute and does what I wanted it to.On to the bad: It doesn't have as much range of motion as another similar lamp I bought years ago but it cost half as much too. Also, the base is a lightweight plastic so treat it with care. it feels brittle.Overall, it is cute, functional and affordable. I enjoy it.

The lamp is a great size for my desk. Very easy to assemble. Easy to twist to different positions and holds the position well. Great brightness.Good delivery - package in great shape.Thank you.

reviews.reviewTitle: Smaller than expected. Needs special bulbs.
reviews.reviewText: Two cons with this lamp:1) It is much shorterr than what the picture would suggest. The length from the base to the first joint is 11", the upper arm is abt 8". When stretched out - from the base to the end of the second arm - 19". Way too small if you need to cover the whole desk/work area.2) The regular sized bulbs are sticking out of the shade like a proverbial thumb (see the photo). This makes lamp not only looking ugly but it's harsh on your eyes as the bulb is exposed. You need a special - much smaller bulb (see the photo).
This lamp base is too light for the lamp. You cannot extend it without risk of it toppling over.Update: the return process was quick and painless.
